WEBVTT

00:00:04.714 --> 00:00:10.052
Is the destiny of mankind controlled
by some transcendental entity or Law?

00:00:10.886 --> 00:00:13.806
Is it like the hand of
God hovering above?

00:00:14.932 --> 00:00:16.726
At least it is true...

00:00:17.143 --> 00:00:20.896
...that man has no
control, even over his own will.

00:00:28.237 --> 00:00:31.407
Go back to the
sheath your master holds.

00:00:31.991 --> 00:00:34.160
Go back to Griffith!

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:42.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

00:00:47.214 --> 00:00:49.842
Don't glower at me like that.

00:00:49.967 --> 00:00:55.598
I'm offering you all the fun you want
right before setting out for the afterlife.

00:01:05.066 --> 00:01:07.818
What's wrong, are you embarrassed?

00:01:14.909 --> 00:01:17.828
I'm unable to push this bastard aside...

00:01:18.454 --> 00:01:19.330
My...

00:01:19.455 --> 00:01:21.791
My arm is so powerless...

00:01:51.070 --> 00:01:52.863
<i>Feel no shame about shape.</i>

00:01:52.988 --> 00:01:54.740
<i>Weather changes the phrase.</i>

00:01:54.949 --> 00:01:58.494
<i>Even mother will
show you another way.</i>

00:01:58.619 --> 00:02:00.871
<i>So, put your glasses on.</i>

00:02:00.996 --> 00:02:02.957
<i>Nothing will be wrong.</i>

00:02:03.082 --> 00:02:05.126
<i>There's no blame, there's no fame.</i>

00:02:05.376 --> 00:02:07.002
<i>It's up to you.</i>

00:02:07.211 --> 00:02:10.673
<i>The first words should be found.</i>

00:02:11.549 --> 00:02:14.301
<i>Whatever holds you back.</i>

00:02:15.052 --> 00:02:15.678
<i>I...</i>

00:02:16.053 --> 00:02:16.762
<i>... can...</i>

00:02:16.887 --> 00:02:18.931
<i>I can get it off.</i>

00:02:19.056 --> 00:02:20.015
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:02:20.182 --> 00:02:20.933
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:02:21.058 --> 00:02:22.810
<i>Tell me what you want.</i>

00:02:23.018 --> 00:02:23.936
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:02:24.145 --> 00:02:24.895
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:02:25.062 --> 00:02:26.897
<i>I don't know why you are afraid.</i>

00:02:27.064 --> 00:02:28.065
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:02:28.190 --> 00:02:29.024
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:02:29.191 --> 00:02:30.651
<i>Tell me what you'd say.</i>

00:02:30.943 --> 00:02:31.944
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:02:32.194 --> 00:02:33.070
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:02:33.195 --> 00:02:33.904
<i>Too late...</i>

00:02:34.029 --> 00:02:35.531
<i>It's too late.</i>

00:02:40.661 --> 00:02:44.665
Bonfire of Dreams

00:02:55.968 --> 00:03:00.055
Don't even think
about biting your tongue off.

00:03:00.347 --> 00:03:03.559
It'd be a shame if you
died before we finished our fun.

00:03:05.436 --> 00:03:10.733
Do you want to die in a place like this?

00:03:12.193 --> 00:03:15.696
Go back to the
sheath your master holds.

00:03:17.698 --> 00:03:19.116
I won't bite my tongue off.

00:03:19.950 --> 00:03:22.369
Oh no, she's been driven to despair.

00:03:22.953 --> 00:03:26.248
Can't you resist a little
so we can get turned on?

00:03:27.499 --> 00:03:28.250
But...

00:03:28.709 --> 00:03:30.502
I won't let you rape me, either!

00:03:30.711 --> 00:03:31.462
What?

00:03:34.506 --> 00:03:35.341
Bitch!

00:03:35.466 --> 00:03:36.967
You'll pay for that!

00:03:45.392 --> 00:03:47.394
I'll kill you dead!

00:03:58.656 --> 00:04:00.282
You better lay off now.

00:04:00.532 --> 00:04:01.408
Judeau!

00:04:01.867 --> 00:04:04.245
She is the only woman in our troop.

00:04:04.995 --> 00:04:06.288
It'll cost you.

00:04:16.882 --> 00:04:18.133
Unbelievable!

00:04:18.259 --> 00:04:21.387
He's beaten almost half my
hundred men in spite of his wounds...

00:04:21.971 --> 00:04:24.348
I admit, this is no fluke.

00:04:25.099 --> 00:04:26.392
What was that?

00:04:27.142 --> 00:04:29.520
There are fifty of you still alive?

00:04:30.396 --> 00:04:34.900
Great, day will dawn by the time I get
around to cracking open all of your heads!

00:04:38.153 --> 00:04:39.029
Don't let up!

00:04:39.363 --> 00:04:41.156
He barely has the strength to stand!

00:04:41.282 --> 00:04:42.491
Defeat him now!

00:04:56.297 --> 00:04:58.299
What am I doing here?

00:04:59.675 --> 00:05:01.552
In a miserable place like this...

00:05:05.389 --> 00:05:07.558
It's not worth risking my life for this...

00:05:08.767 --> 00:05:10.185
Am I fighting for Caska?

00:05:14.690 --> 00:05:16.692
No, that can't be it...

00:05:18.694 --> 00:05:20.571
I don't have time to think now.

00:05:21.447 --> 00:05:23.032
I should concentrate
on wielding my sword...

00:05:23.824 --> 00:05:24.783
...and killing...

00:05:24.908 --> 00:05:25.826
...nothing more...

00:05:37.463 --> 00:05:38.672
Sorry, I was late.

00:05:39.340 --> 00:05:42.593
It took quite a bit of time to persuade
those big shots we needed to rescue you.

00:05:44.720 --> 00:05:45.471
H-Hey...

00:05:46.555 --> 00:05:47.681
You must run...

00:05:48.974 --> 00:05:49.975
He...

00:05:50.100 --> 00:05:51.310
Guts...

00:05:51.852 --> 00:05:52.603
Hurry!

00:05:52.811 --> 00:05:54.438
What happened to Guts?

00:05:55.230 --> 00:05:56.732
This way, quickly!

00:05:57.983 --> 00:05:59.610
Someone, give her your shoulder!

00:06:00.110 --> 00:06:01.570
I don't need it!

00:06:02.321 --> 00:06:03.322
He...

00:06:03.614 --> 00:06:07.076
He stayed in the midst of the
enemy to help me get away...

00:06:07.993 --> 00:06:09.453
We've got to hurry, or...

00:06:14.500 --> 00:06:15.250
Let's move!

00:06:16.960 --> 00:06:17.878
I will make it...

00:06:19.963 --> 00:06:21.090
I have to make it...

00:06:34.728 --> 00:06:35.771
Here it is!

00:06:51.161 --> 00:06:53.163
Oh, my God...

00:06:54.790 --> 00:06:56.291
Is this for real?

00:06:56.500 --> 00:06:58.377
I see almost a hundred men lying here.

00:06:58.919 --> 00:07:01.505
Did he really do all this by himself?

00:07:15.936 --> 00:07:16.812
Guts...

00:07:19.690 --> 00:07:20.691
Guts!

00:07:39.460 --> 00:07:40.335
Guts!

00:07:41.920 --> 00:07:42.212
Guts!

00:07:42.212 --> 00:07:42.796
Those look like deadly wounds...
Guts!

00:07:42.796 --> 00:07:43.464
Those look like deadly wounds...

00:07:43.589 --> 00:07:44.423
Guts!

00:07:44.590 --> 00:07:46.467
Come on, you've only joking, right?

00:07:46.592 --> 00:07:47.718
Hey, Guts!

00:07:48.302 --> 00:07:49.344
Guts!

00:07:50.053 --> 00:07:50.971
Guts!

00:07:57.603 --> 00:07:59.313
Stop shaking me...

00:08:00.314 --> 00:08:02.483
It's not helping my wounds...

00:08:03.859 --> 00:08:04.860
Guts...

00:08:06.570 --> 00:08:07.488
Out of the way now!

00:08:07.613 --> 00:08:08.697
Move it!

00:08:09.239 --> 00:08:10.240
It's an emergency!

00:08:10.365 --> 00:08:11.366
Make way for us!

00:08:11.492 --> 00:08:13.118
It's no big deal!

00:08:13.243 --> 00:08:14.578
I can walk on my own!

00:08:14.745 --> 00:08:16.497
Don't move, you'll
make your wounds worse!

00:08:16.872 --> 00:08:18.582
Hey, they're back!

00:08:18.999 --> 00:08:21.376
Dammit, he was alive after all.

00:08:21.627 --> 00:08:22.753
Guts!

00:08:24.588 --> 00:08:26.006
Hey, ouch!

00:08:26.131 --> 00:08:27.633
That hurts!

00:08:28.258 --> 00:08:31.512
You'll heal faster without
anesthetic, so just bear it.

00:08:31.720 --> 00:08:32.930
Shit!

00:08:33.138 --> 00:08:34.932
I'm not a torn shirt you're sewing up!

00:08:35.307 --> 00:08:37.392
Okay, I'm done now.

00:08:40.020 --> 00:08:41.522
What a guy!

00:08:41.939 --> 00:08:46.777
With wounds like yours, most men
wouldn't be able to stay conscious.

00:08:47.027 --> 00:08:48.695
How's his condition?

00:08:49.071 --> 00:08:53.909
Well, he's no longer in danger but
I prescribe total bedrest for him!

00:08:54.326 --> 00:08:55.953
Total bed rest?

00:08:56.578 --> 00:08:58.956
Then what you're saying is...

00:08:59.915 --> 00:09:02.960
He should be left behind when the
army breaks camp and moves out.

00:09:03.085 --> 00:09:04.044
No way!

00:09:04.211 --> 00:09:05.212
Bullshit!

00:09:05.420 --> 00:09:07.965
I'll stick with you all until the
end, even if I have to crawl after you!

00:09:08.090 --> 00:09:09.091
Ridiculous!

00:09:09.299 --> 00:09:12.094
You will seriously endanger your
life if you rejoin the front lines now!

00:09:12.719 --> 00:09:14.721
Endanger my life?

00:09:14.805 --> 00:09:17.224
I put my life in danger
every time I go to war.

00:09:17.349 --> 00:09:18.976
It's out of the question!

00:09:19.101 --> 00:09:20.102
Oh, suit yourself!

00:09:27.859 --> 00:09:29.987
Now, everything's settled, all right?

00:09:30.195 --> 00:09:32.614
The two of you are back and safe.

00:09:36.827 --> 00:09:38.370
Where is Griffith, anyway?

00:09:38.745 --> 00:09:41.331
Griffith is at
headquarters for the war counsel.

00:09:41.498 --> 00:09:43.083
He set out this morning.

00:09:43.208 --> 00:09:43.875
Oh, no.

00:09:44.209 --> 00:09:46.378
He won't come back until tomorrow.

00:09:48.839 --> 00:09:50.841
And they finally came back, too.

00:09:50.966 --> 00:09:52.509
What bad timing!

00:09:54.636 --> 00:09:57.014
Caska, aren't you
going to get looked at?

00:09:58.223 --> 00:09:59.474
I'm fine.

00:10:00.225 --> 00:10:02.644
I didn't get injured...

00:10:04.605 --> 00:10:07.024
But you had a fever, didn't you?

00:10:07.149 --> 00:10:07.983
Oh!

00:10:08.108 --> 00:10:09.401
What's going on?

00:10:22.539 --> 00:10:25.375
Seriously, we were worried
that the worst might have happened.

00:10:25.792 --> 00:10:29.546
For once, we need to
thank Commander Guts.

00:10:29.755 --> 00:10:32.299
Sorry for having worried you all.

00:10:32.424 --> 00:10:34.009
I'm glad you're safe, Big Sister.

00:10:34.801 --> 00:10:37.763
But Captain Griffith is cold at heart.

00:10:38.305 --> 00:10:40.766
He just left for a war
counsel or something.

00:10:40.891 --> 00:10:41.808
Watch your mouth.

00:10:42.142 --> 00:10:44.061
Oh, I am sorry, Big Sister...

00:10:46.396 --> 00:10:47.189
Caska.

00:10:48.023 --> 00:10:49.900
Can I have your ear for a moment?

00:10:55.072 --> 00:10:56.073
What's the matter?

00:10:56.531 --> 00:10:59.034
Well, I want to tell you this.

00:11:01.203 --> 00:11:05.957
When I asked Griffith to send a search
party so we could rescue the two of you...

00:11:06.833 --> 00:11:10.587
...those nobles spoke against
us, making objections of all kinds.

00:11:11.797 --> 00:11:12.798
But...

00:11:13.465 --> 00:11:15.467
Griffith really put his foot down.

00:11:16.343 --> 00:11:18.595
Those two are key for the Hawks.

00:11:19.096 --> 00:11:20.597
I will never lose them.

00:11:21.098 --> 00:11:22.307
Griffith said that...

00:11:23.558 --> 00:11:25.435
Yeah, he said that for you.

00:11:25.811 --> 00:11:28.105
It's amazing how
much he values you two.

00:11:29.481 --> 00:11:32.317
Honestly, I felt little jealous.

00:11:42.619 --> 00:11:44.746
Oh, hey, I almost forgot about this.

00:11:46.707 --> 00:11:49.376
Give this to the big guy
who killed a hundred men.

00:11:50.335 --> 00:11:51.253
It's medicine?

00:11:52.713 --> 00:11:55.882
I got this from a company of
travelling players I used to work for.

00:11:56.383 --> 00:11:58.260
You may not believe it...

00:11:58.593 --> 00:12:00.721
...but it is made from fairy dust.

00:12:01.012 --> 00:12:02.139
Fairy dust?

00:12:02.597 --> 00:12:03.473
That's impossible!

00:12:03.765 --> 00:12:05.267
I know you doubt it.

00:12:05.642 --> 00:12:08.395
But it works wonders
and the effect is guaranteed.

00:12:08.645 --> 00:12:12.023
It saved my life a
couple times, trust me.

00:12:12.482 --> 00:12:14.401
Such a precious thing of yours...

00:12:14.776 --> 00:12:15.902
Don't worry.

00:12:16.111 --> 00:12:20.407
I think it's a pretty good deal, we got
a hundred men for one pack of medicine.

00:12:27.914 --> 00:12:29.416
Thank you, Judeau.

00:12:34.796 --> 00:12:38.300
She suddenly became
like an ordinary girl, didn't she?

00:12:40.427 --> 00:12:41.386
Guts...

00:13:07.829 --> 00:13:08.830
Guts...

00:13:35.357 --> 00:13:36.566
What's going on?

00:13:39.736 --> 00:13:41.696
Wouldn't it be better if you slept?

00:13:46.117 --> 00:13:48.829
I can't sleep
because my body is burning.

00:13:49.454 --> 00:13:52.624
Up here I feel at
ease, and it's much cooler.

00:13:58.630 --> 00:13:59.381
Hey...

00:13:59.506 --> 00:14:00.382
Don't move.

00:14:19.526 --> 00:14:20.735
The pain...

00:14:21.027 --> 00:14:22.112
...is subsiding.

00:14:25.031 --> 00:14:26.283
What is this?

00:14:26.658 --> 00:14:28.243
Judeau gave it to me.

00:14:28.660 --> 00:14:30.495
It's some kind of secret medicine.

00:14:31.121 --> 00:14:32.622
Now, turn your back.

00:14:41.673 --> 00:14:42.757
You know...

00:14:42.924 --> 00:14:44.759
...there's nothing for
you to worry yourself over.

00:14:45.927 --> 00:14:48.179
I brought myself to
do that for my own sake.

00:14:48.805 --> 00:14:51.141
It wasn't for you in particular.

00:14:54.436 --> 00:14:58.940
I'd rather fight with my sword
than run away, it's my nature.

00:14:59.399 --> 00:15:00.817
That was the only reason...

00:15:01.818 --> 00:15:06.448
You fought a hundred men with
your sword because it's your nature?

00:15:12.704 --> 00:15:14.706
Yeah, that's it.

00:15:16.291 --> 00:15:19.085
Besides, I had to give
that bastard some payback.

00:15:19.920 --> 00:15:23.924
I didn't remember anything clearly because
I had lost myself in swinging my sword.

00:15:26.718 --> 00:15:31.306
But, to tell the truth, there was
something I couldn't get out of my head...

00:15:32.057 --> 00:15:34.184
Compared to what you're doing...

00:15:34.726 --> 00:15:36.978
...what I did, fighting
against a hundred men...

00:15:37.103 --> 00:15:38.480
...was nothing.

00:15:48.239 --> 00:15:51.242
Not only you, but Griffith too...

00:15:52.369 --> 00:15:55.705
The two of you have something
really important to stake your life on.

00:15:56.373 --> 00:15:58.750
I think it's great, I mean it.

00:16:01.586 --> 00:16:03.254
Compared to your purpose...

00:16:03.380 --> 00:16:07.759
...my fighting against a hundred
men or a thousand is just random.

00:16:07.884 --> 00:16:09.010
It's no big deal at all.

00:16:10.136 --> 00:16:11.221
Guts...

00:16:15.642 --> 00:16:17.143
Some view, huh?

00:16:19.604 --> 00:16:22.148
Gaston doesn't think
he's very suited to army life.

00:16:22.607 --> 00:16:24.025
He wants to start...

00:16:24.234 --> 00:16:27.404
...a tailoring business with the
money he's earned after the war.

00:16:28.029 --> 00:16:30.490
He's good with his hands,
though he may not look it.

00:16:31.866 --> 00:16:33.868
Nichole proposed
to a woman, but she refused.

00:16:33.994 --> 00:16:36.621
She didn't want
to marry a common soldier.

00:16:36.788 --> 00:16:39.666
He wants to get promoted as soon
as possible, so he can ask her again.

00:16:40.750 --> 00:16:43.545
That's why he is reckless and
tends to overextend himself in battle.

00:16:44.879 --> 00:16:48.425
Well, everyone seems to
stake their life on lost causes.

00:16:52.303 --> 00:16:58.768
Looking over all of them from
here, it makes me think that I can see...

00:16:59.310 --> 00:17:02.647
...all their little dreams and hopes...

00:17:03.189 --> 00:17:04.899
...flickering in each light.

00:17:09.904 --> 00:17:13.158
Like a bonfire of dreams...

00:17:13.867 --> 00:17:15.785
That was beautiful...

00:17:15.910 --> 00:17:17.871
I thought it was the princess talking.

00:17:17.996 --> 00:17:18.663
Don't say that!

00:17:20.665 --> 00:17:22.417
But, you are right.

00:17:22.917 --> 00:17:24.627
I think that each one of them...

00:17:24.753 --> 00:17:29.174
...brings their own wisps of
light when they gather together.

00:17:29.632 --> 00:17:35.513
Yeah, and so those
fragile lights don't go out...

00:17:36.056 --> 00:17:39.309
...they throw their lights
into the strongest flame of all...

00:17:42.520 --> 00:17:45.690
A powerful fire called Griffith...

00:17:49.277 --> 00:17:50.278
But...

00:17:50.820 --> 00:17:52.405
...my light cannot be seen among them.

00:17:55.909 --> 00:18:02.457
I guess I'm just someone who
stopped to warm up by the bonfire.

00:18:02.957 --> 00:18:03.958
Guts...

00:18:09.339 --> 00:18:13.676
As long as I have my sword to fight
with, I am sure to survive any battle.

00:18:14.594 --> 00:18:16.971
It's a fact, year after year I prove it true.

00:18:18.098 --> 00:18:22.227
Before joining the
Hawks, I always survived...

00:18:22.477 --> 00:18:24.604
...even in hopeless, losing battles.

00:18:25.230 --> 00:18:26.606
It happened again this time...

00:18:27.816 --> 00:18:31.945
But, doing that kind of
thing is not really important.

00:18:33.196 --> 00:18:35.990
I've been fighting in battles
for as long as I can remember.

00:18:36.616 --> 00:18:39.077
The mercenary leader who raised me...

00:18:39.369 --> 00:18:42.497
...taught me nothing
except how to wield a sword.

00:18:43.456 --> 00:18:45.959
I've never had
anything except my sword.

00:18:46.709 --> 00:18:48.253
I don't want to die.

00:18:48.878 --> 00:18:51.506
But for me, that was
the only reason for fighting.

00:18:52.090 --> 00:18:54.884
I found myself fighting because...

00:18:55.635 --> 00:18:57.595
...I know nothing but how to wield this.

00:19:00.098 --> 00:19:04.477
Above all, I was ready to just
commit myself to fighting back there...

00:19:05.520 --> 00:19:08.273
...and leave finding a real
reason to fight up to the others.

00:19:09.149 --> 00:19:10.233
Guts...

00:19:12.485 --> 00:19:15.655
Anyway, I guess all
that sounds kind of dumb.

00:19:15.780 --> 00:19:17.866
I'm wondering why I told you all that...

00:19:18.408 --> 00:19:19.784
It's pretty pathetic.

00:19:20.160 --> 00:19:21.536
So am I.

00:19:25.415 --> 00:19:26.416
Guts...

00:19:26.666 --> 00:19:28.042
...are you thinking of...

00:19:36.050 --> 00:19:39.804
Are you going to leave the Hawks?

00:19:50.398 --> 00:19:51.191
Guts...

00:19:51.649 --> 00:19:55.820
I said that I was going to fight
this war to the end, no matter what.

00:19:56.654 --> 00:19:58.573
What will you do afterwards?

00:19:59.073 --> 00:20:00.200
Guts!

00:20:00.575 --> 00:20:01.451
Caska!

00:20:03.828 --> 00:20:05.288
Griffith is back!

00:20:06.164 --> 00:20:07.707
He heard that you were safe...

00:20:07.832 --> 00:20:10.418
...so he changed his schedule
to come back here a day early!

00:20:14.839 --> 00:20:16.049
Welcome back!

00:20:17.842 --> 00:20:18.343
Captain!

00:20:18.468 --> 00:20:19.219
Glad you're safe!

00:20:19.344 --> 00:20:20.803
Oh, Commander Guts!

00:20:27.227 --> 00:20:27.852
Hey.

00:20:33.858 --> 00:20:35.818
Griffith, I apologize.

00:20:36.236 --> 00:20:39.697
I held everyone back, it's my fault...

00:20:40.323 --> 00:20:42.367
Despite my physical condition...

00:20:42.575 --> 00:20:45.119
...I went into battle and
caused everything to go wrong.

00:20:45.328 --> 00:20:47.997
I even put my entire company in danger.

00:20:48.581 --> 00:20:51.626
Not only that, I put Guts
and his Raiders in danger as well.

00:20:52.126 --> 00:20:54.128
I'm not qualified to be a commander!

00:20:54.212 --> 00:20:55.338
I will accept any punishment...

00:20:56.631 --> 00:20:58.591
W-What are you doing, you idiot!

00:21:04.764 --> 00:21:05.890
Welcome back.

00:21:12.605 --> 00:21:14.232
Go for it, Commander!

00:21:15.233 --> 00:21:16.651
Jump on me, too!

00:21:16.901 --> 00:21:19.279
All right, let's all go and get a drink!

00:21:19.654 --> 00:21:20.613
Are you sure, Commander?

00:21:20.863 --> 00:21:22.031
In your condition?

00:21:22.907 --> 00:21:25.785
Shut up, I'm just going
to disinfect my body liquor!

00:21:25.910 --> 00:21:27.537
I'm not responsible for this.

00:21:27.662 --> 00:21:29.289
Let's celebrate the hundred-man fight!

00:21:30.164 --> 00:21:31.040
What's the matter?

00:21:32.417 --> 00:21:33.251
Nothing...

00:21:34.294 --> 00:21:35.295
Is he...

00:21:36.170 --> 00:21:37.672
...serious about leaving?

00:22:02.947 --> 00:22:05.074
<i>Looking back, the morning comes.</i>

00:22:05.199 --> 00:22:08.703
<i>Don't find your face in your glass.</i>

00:22:09.954 --> 00:22:12.790
<i>Take the moonlight by the tail.</i>

00:22:12.832 --> 00:22:15.710
<i>It's a rainy sight that you're shading.</i>

00:22:17.462 --> 00:22:18.963
<i>What is that?</i>

00:22:19.088 --> 00:22:20.214
<i>It's just the same.</i>

00:22:20.340 --> 00:22:23.426
<i>What is trying on your crown?</i>

00:22:24.719 --> 00:22:27.597
<i>I'm spending my
glass and walking back.</i>

00:22:27.722 --> 00:22:30.933
<i>So wear my glass, you're fading.</i>

00:22:31.225 --> 00:22:34.562
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:34.979 --> 00:22:37.940
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:38.608 --> 00:22:41.611
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:42.487 --> 00:22:45.323
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:46.240 --> 00:22:49.118
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:49.994 --> 00:22:51.829
<i>I'm waiting...</i>

00:23:06.886 --> 00:23:08.888
Next Episode

00:23:09.597 --> 00:23:14.143
Someday, a man will have to
forget something he once possessed.

00:23:15.144 --> 00:23:19.774
Someday, a man will have to
climb over a wall that stands before him.

00:23:20.900 --> 00:23:24.904
He will keep his head high and
strain his eyes toward the horizon...

00:23:25.738 --> 00:23:27.657
...as he keeps charging forward.

00:23:28.157 --> 00:23:31.869
In this world, does being young mean
that matters of life and death are transient?

00:23:33.913 --> 00:23:36.916
The Decisive Battle

